  geom_boxplot(mapping = aes(x= cut, y = carat)) + coord_flip()

ggplot(data = diamonds) +
  geom_boxplot(mapping = aes(x = cut,y = carat, fill = color, position = "dodge") ) + ggtitle ("Diamond Dataset") + xlab( "CUT OF DIAMOND") + ylab("CARAT OF DIAMOND") + coord_flip()

ggplot(data = diamonds) +
  geom_boxplot(mapping = aes(x = cut,y = carat, fill = color)) + ggtitle ("Diamond Dataset") + theme_bw() + theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 14, family = "Tahoma", face = "bold")) + xlab( "CUT OF DIAMOND") + ylab("CARAT OF DIAMOND") + coord_flip()
